---
/**
 * /contribute — onboarding for new pack authors + submitters.
 *
 * Design-review D-14. Satisfies the Persona A journey gap the design
 * review called out: "creator who wants to publish" had no surface.
 *
 * Content-heavy, zero interactive state. Zero client-JS. Pure SSG.
 * A `pretext-templates submit` CLI subcommand is aspirational here —
 * the page describes the contract, the CLI lands in a later commit.
 */

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---

<Layout
  title="Contribute · pretext-templates"
  description="How to add your own pack to the pretext-templates registry — from zero to a merged PR in under 30 minutes."
>
  <article class="contribute container">
    <header class="contribute__head">
      <p class="meta">Contribute</p>
      <h1>Add your pack.</h1>
      <p class="contribute__lede">
        pretext-templates is MIT-licensed and deliberately built to be
        forked. If your pack fits the warm-analog brief, the registry
        would love to carry it. From clone to merged PR in under thirty
        minutes.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="contribute__section">
      <h2>1 · What fits</h2>
      <p>
        A pretext-templates pack is <em>one HTML file</em> that renders
        to a PDF. Self-contained styles. A single <code>manifest.json</code>
        describing it. That's it.
      </p>
      <ul class="contribute__checklist">
        <li>✔ Warm analog-leaning typography (serif primary · one accent)</li>
        <li>✔ Prints cleanly in A4 or Letter</li>
        <li>✔ Works on GoodNotes 6 / Notability / Noteshelf / CollaNote</li>
        <li>✔ MIT-licensed or a compatible permissive license</li>
        <li>✔ No JavaScript in the template itself (print fidelity)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="contribute__section">
      <h2>2 · Clone + scaffold</h2>
      <pre class="contribute__code">
<code>git clone {SITE.repoUrl}
cd pretext-templates
npm ci
npm run dev                           # starts the gallery preview</code></pre>

      <p>
        Once the dev server is up, the CLI scaffolder creates a new
        pack directory with a blank template + <code>manifest.json</code>:
      </p>

      <pre class="contribute__code">
<code>npx @pretext-templates/cli init my-pack-id --category worksheet</code></pre>

      <p class="meta contribute__note">
        The <code>init</code> subcommand is on the W11 milestone; until
        it lands, copy the <code>packages/packs-eat-the-frog/</code>
        directory and rename it as a starting point.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contribute__section">
      <h2>3 · manifest.json contract</h2>
      <p>
        Every pack owns a <code>manifest.json</code> that validates against
        the Zod schema in
        <code>packages/core/src/types/registry.ts</code>. The minimum is:
      </p>
      <pre class="contribute__code">
<code>{`{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "id": "my-pack-id",
  "name": "My Pack",
  "description": "One-line summary ≤ 140 chars.",
  "category": "worksheet",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "author": "Your GitHub handle",
  "entry": "my-pack-id.html",
  "license": "MIT",
  "tags": ["worksheet", "your-tag"]
}`}</code></pre>

      <p>
        <code>id</code> must match the directory name exactly
        (<code>packages/packs-<strong>&lt;id&gt;</strong>/</code>).
        Kebab-case only. The build-time validator at
        <code>apps/gallery/scripts/validate-pack-ids.ts</code> enforces
        this on every run.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contribute__section">
      <h2>4 · Check before PR</h2>
      <pre class="contribute__code">
<code>npm test                              # 211 unit tests must stay green
npm run test:e2e                      # 25 Playwright smokes must pass
npx tsc -b                            # TypeScript clean
npx astro check                       # 0 errors</code></pre>

      <p>
        If all four pass, you're in the clear. The registry regenerates
        automatically; the gallery picks up your MDX stub (one file, next
        to the others in <code>apps/gallery/src/content/packs/</code>).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contribute__section">
      <h2>5 · Submit</h2>
      <p>
        Open a PR at <a href={SITE.repoUrl + '/compare'}>{SITE.domain}</a>.
        The PR template asks for a one-line pack description, a screenshot
        of the rendered PDF, and a checkbox confirming the WCAG 2.2 AA
        audit on the template itself (contrast ≥ 4.5:1 on body copy).
      </p>
      <p>
        Every PR runs the same four checks above in CI; green = ready
        for review. First-pass review typically lands within 48 hours.
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <footer class="contribute__footer meta">
      <p>
        Questions? Open a discussion at
        <a href={SITE.repoUrl + '/discussions'}>{SITE.domain}/discussions</a>.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .contribute {
    padding-top: 48px;
    padding-bottom: 48px;
    max-width: 780px;
  }
  .contribute__head {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }
  .contribute__head h1 {
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  .contribute__lede {
    font-family: var(--italic);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-top: 16px;
    max-width: 58ch;
  }
  .contribute__section {
    margin: 40px 0;
  }
  .contribute__section h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .contribute__section p {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .contribute__checklist {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 16px 0;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .contribute__checklist li {
    padding: 6px 0;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .contribute__code {
    background: var(--paper-dark);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--sage);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin: 16px 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .contribute__code code {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    background: transparent;
  }
  .contribute__note {
    margin-top: 8px;
    font-style: italic;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .contribute__footer {
    margin-top: 48px;
  }
</style>
